"Tomé A.R., Miranda P.M.A.","Continuous partial trends and low-frequency oscillations of time series",2005,"Nonlinear Processes in Geophysics","12","4",,"451","460",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-22744453055&partnerID=40&md5=115d5867303e32ec67b21341823a97e5","Universidade da Beira Interior, Department of Physics, Centro de Geofísica, Lisboa, Portugal; University of Lisbon, Faculdade de Ciências, Centro de Geofísica, Lisbon, Portugal","Tomé, A.R., Universidade da Beira Interior, Department of Physics, Centro de Geofísica, Lisboa, Portugal; Miranda, P.M.A., University of Lisbon, Faculdade de Ciências, Centro de Geofísica, Lisbon, Portugal","This paper presents a recent methodology developed for the analysis of the slow evolution of geophysical time series. The method is based on least-squares fitting of continuous line segments to the data, subject to flexible conditions, and is able to objectively locate the times of significant change in the series tendencies. The time distribution of these breakpoints may be an important set of parameters for the analysis of the long term evolution of some geophysical data, simplifying the intercomparison between datasets and offering a new way for the analysis of time varying spatially distributed data. Several application examples, using data that is important in the context of global warming studies, are presented and briefly discussed. © 2005 Author(s). This work is licensed under a Creative Commons License.",,"time series analysis",,,,,,"Basist, A.N., Chelliah, M., Comparison of tropospheric temperatures derived from the NCEP/NCAR reanalysis, NCEP operational analysis and the Microwave Sounding Unit (1997) Bull. Am. Met. Soc., 78, pp. 1431-1447; Bloomfield, P., Trend in global temperature (1992) Climate Change, 21, pp. 1-16; Bloomfield, P., Nychka, D.W., Climate spectra and detecting climate change (1992) Climate Change, 21, pp. 275-287; Bouaricha, A., Schnabel, R.B., Equations and Nonlinear Leastsquare